<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1436,1343,1594]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1418,1444]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[288,540,1419,1444]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Hygrobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ezoensis">
<emphasis box="[288,540,1419,1444]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Hygrobates ezoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species known from Hokkaido (
<collectingCountry box="[972,1045,1418,1444]" name="Japan" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Japan</collectingCountry>
) and Sakhalin, was reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ozkan" box="[151,312,1456,1482]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" refString="Ozkan, M. (1982) Dogu Anadolu Su Akarlari (Acari, Hydrachnellae) Uzerine Sistematik Arastirmalar-II. Ataturk Univertesi, Fen Fakultesi Dergisi, 1, 145 - 163." type="journal article" year="1982">
Özkan (
<number box="[242,303,1456,1482]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" value="1982.0">1982</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
based on female specimen (s) but never found again since then. Most probably this record refers to 
<emphasis box="[180,362,1493,1518]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">H. diversiporus</emphasis>
Sokolow, a species described from the Caucasus. According to 
<bibRefCitation box="[1109,1392,1493,1519]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" refString="Matsumoto, N., Dick, M. H. &amp; Mawatari, S. F. (2005) Water mites of the genus Hygrobates Koch, 1837 (Acari: Parasitengona: Hygrobatidae) from Hokkaido, northern Japan. Journal of Natural History, 39, 1893 - 1945." type="journal article">
Matsumoto 
<emphasis box="[1250,1301,1493,1518]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[1323,1385,1493,1519]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
the male genital plate seems to be the salient difference between 
<taxonomicName box="[900,1039,1531,1556]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Hygrobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ezoensis">
<emphasis box="[900,1039,1531,1556]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">H. ezoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1100,1288,1531,1556]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">H. diversiporus</emphasis>
, as no clear diagnostic differences in the female or other characters can be found.
</paragraph>
